[2026-05-18T10:00:00+01:00] CRITICAL_PATH_REVIEW — domain=version-pipeline evidence="M4's critical path is the cz bump + tag + push release pipeline. Validated in 4 ways: (1) Pre-bump state captured — `uv run cz version` = 4.13.9 (commitizen installed in venv; M0 context-log noted this was a gap, resolved by uv sync at some point between M0 and M4). (2) Dry-run validated bump shape — `cz bump --increment MINOR --dry-run` returned `bump: version 0.9.0 → 0.10.0` + `tag to create: v0.10.0`. (3) Real bump: committed as `25d4fbe bump: version 0.9.0 → 0.10.0`. CHANGELOG auto-regenerated from commit-log per commitizen convention (the detailed `[Unreleased]` prose I authored in Step 4.4 was supplanted; ADR-0007 carries the full detail — this is the L-006-derived convention: changelog stays terse + cz-derived, architectural detail lives in ADRs). (4) Tag + main pushed via `git push origin v0.10.0` (explicit) + `git push origin main --follow-tags` (annotated tags). Remote-verified: `25d4fbe938ef0ea20bb4314da87462f27e22c166 refs/tags/v0.10.0`. `uv run aa-ma-tui --version` returns `aa-ma-tui 0.10.0` (importlib.metadata picks up the new version after `uv sync`). NO dual-pipeline conflict (cz owns the bump; python-semantic-release pin `>=9.0` is satisfied but not invoked at release time). NO hand-edits to version in pyproject.toml or src/aa_ma/__init__.py (Wave-1 CRITICAL #3 from Phase 4.5 verification, mitigated)." — reviewer=lead-orchestrator
